      "comment": "PAW RENALLA (6) produced a modest effort most recently when sixth at Ballarat over 390m behind Paw Gusto (22.94) in a Grade 5. Tough to beat if on-song. RABADA (4) has missed the placings at his last two but was third at Shepparton three back and returns to Bendigo where he tends to run well. Has the ability and expected to do much better. COLLINDA POPS (8) has been mixing form lately, hitting the frame two back before finishing fourth (24.46) at this track in a Grade 5. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. BRODIE'S SHADOW (1) is worth consideration after filling a hole at big odds last start.",
